thability, and protection for winter</h3> <p>Looking for a layer that actually handles the cold? A fleece pullover traps air between its fibres, and that trapped air is what keeps you warm during winter activities. Simple concept, but it works. The focus here is warmth without giving up protection from wind and weather.</p> <h3>Materials, designs and technical features for skiing</h3> <p>The polyester fleeces we use are warm, comfortable, and great at letting moisture escape from your skin. So you stay dry, not damp and clammy, even in cold weather outdoors. They keep you protected when it counts.</p> <h3>From lightweight midlayers to thick shearlings</h3> <p>Quick-drying and easy to clean, too. The lightweight, breathable ski fleeces are the best midlayers for a day in the mountains. And the thick, warm shearlings? Perfect as a fleece jacket for cold winter nights at the ski hills or a walk through the city. Stylish either way.</p> <p>Zipped or unzipped, we've got both. They work for colder and milder conditions alike. Casual sweaters come in different styles too, and we sell a variety of accessories to go with everything.</p> <h2>Get the latest colour options and choose your women's fleece style</h2> <p>Colours go from black, white, blue, grey, and green all the way to prints and patterns. Sizes range from XS to XL. Check out the new winter collections of women's fleeces at Dopesnow.com, pick your favourite: hooded, high collar, or half zip. Choose the colour or pattern you like, match it all to your ski equipment, and get ready for the snowy season.</p></div></div><div id=\"layout-colors\" style=\"position: absolute; left: 0px; right: 0px; overscroll-behavior: contain; visibility: hidden;\"></div><button class=\"intercom-button\" aria-label=\"Open chat\"><div><svg class=\"intercom-svg\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 0 28 32\"><path d=\"M28 32s-4.714-1.855-8.527-3.34H3.437C1.54 28.66 0 27.026 0 25.013V3.644C0 1.633 1.54 0 3.437 0h21.125c1.898 0 